TITLE: Prince William, Kate Middleton cancel first stop on Caribbean tour after locals hold protest about colonialism
SUMMARY: The start of Prince William and Kate Middleton's royal tour in the Caribbean was marred by controversy after protests about colonialism forced the couple to cancel their first stop in Belize.

TITLE: Feminists protesting Lia Thomas say they are politically homeless: 'Democrats don't care about women'
SUMMARY: A group of feminists protesting outside the women's NCAA swimming championships told Fox News they have "walked away" from the Democratic Party and believe many others have as well.

TITLE: NASA image depicts historic debris cloud from clash of celestial bodies
SUMMARY: NASA has shared an image depicting what researchers say is the first observation of a debris cloud from a massive celestial collision.

TITLE: Dana Perino of Fox News: It's a 'gift to live in a free country with choices to make'
SUMMARY: Dana Perino spoke to Fox News Digital as the new paperback edition of her best-selling book, "Everything Will Be Okay," went on sale in March 2022; this is part 2 of a Q&A with her about life lessons and much more.

TITLE: Firing-squad executions get green light in South Carolina
SUMMARY: South Carolina has given the green light to firing squad executions, a method codified into state law last year after a decade-long pause in carrying out death sentences because of the state’s inability to procure lethal injection drugs.

TITLE: Federal judge says Yale Law students who disrupted free speech panel should be 'noted': email
SUMMARY: A federal judge has warned against hiring Yale Law School students in an email to colleagues, according to a report.

TITLE: Russia claims it used hypersonic missile to strike Ukraine munitions warehouse
SUMMARY: Russia on Saturday said it used a hypersonic Kinzhal missile to strike a Ukrainian munitions warehouse in the western region of Ivano-Frankivsk.

TITLE: WHO chief: Access to Mariupol, other besieged areas of Ukraine now 'critical'
SUMMARY: The World Health Organization (WHO) chief said Thursday that access to Ukraine's besieged city of Mariupol and other embattled areas is now "critical."

TITLE: March Madness 2022: Tyrese Hunter scores 23 as Iowa State edges LSU in NCAA tourney
SUMMARY: Iowa State turned to Tyrese Hunter at the very end, and the freshman delivered.

TITLE: March Madness 2022: Kyler Edwards scores 25 to power Houston past UAB in NCAA opener
SUMMARY: Houston looks like a problem again.

TITLE: 'Real Housewives' star Luann de Lesseps apologizes after alcohol-fueled incident at NYC bar
SUMMARY: Luann de Lesseps says she's in recovery, just days after making headlines for an alcohol-fueled incident at a New York City bar.

TITLE: March Madness 2022: TCU gets first NCAA win since 1987 with rout of Seton Hall
SUMMARY: Mike Miles Jr. scored 21 points and ninth-seeded TCU got its first NCAA Tournament victory in 35 years, easily dispatching eighth-seeded Seton Hall 69-42 on Friday night.

TITLE: Britney Spears returns to Instagram 2 days after account disappeared
SUMMARY: Britney Spears returned to Instagram two days briefly suspending her account earlier this week.

TITLE: March Madness 2022: Michigan State survives, edges Davidson 74-73 in NCAAs
SUMMARY: Michigan State was tough enough to take back the lead in a critical moment, then fortunate enough to withstand Davidson's desperate final charge.

TITLE: March Madness 2022: Wisconsin outlasts Colgate 67-60 as Johnny Davis leads comeback
SUMMARY: Johnny Davis offered a simple explanation for how Wisconsin stepped up down the stretch to avoid a first-round upset.

TITLE: California congressional candidate, former Brooklyn prosecutor on mission to 'defend the American Dream'
SUMMARY: California congressional candidate and former prosecutor Matt Jacobs is on a mission to defend the American Dream.

TITLE: Disgraced ex-NY Gov. Andrew Cuomo is plotting a comeback and it's both horrifying and amazing
SUMMARY: A mere seven months after what seemed like half the women in former Gov. Andrew Cuomo's orbit credibly accused him of harassment, forcing him to resign, he’s making a comeback.

TITLE: COVID-19 pandemic 'far from over,' WHO says
SUMMARY: A World Health Organization (WHO) spokesperson said on Friday that the end of the COVID-19 pandemic was a long way off, citing a rise in cases in its latest weekly data.

TITLE: China reports first COVID-19 deaths in over a year
SUMMARY: China’s health authorities reported two COVID-19 deaths on Saturday, the first since January 2021, as the country battles its worst outbreak in two years driven by a surge in the highly transmissible omicron variant.

TITLE: Biden's weakness in Ukraine-Russia conflict has only further emboldened China in a new kind of war
SUMMARY: Whether we like it or not, the most important theater in Putin’s war in Ukraine is neither Kyiv nor Moscow, but Beijing. If Biden doesn’t have the grit and determination to deal with the CCP, then he’ll never be able to deal with Putin.
